 :tx/rationale "C9-COMPONENT-2: Observation dependency extraction — parse prose references into datom links. PROBLEM: Audit observations contain prose dependency references like 'interacts with F-INV-001', 'requires F-C8-001 as prerequisite', 'strengthens F-TYPE-001'. These are valuable dependency information locked in unstructured text. The store can't traverse them because they're not datom references — they're substring patterns in :exploration/body. The dependency graph between findings is invisible to the query engine. JUSTIFICATION: The trace scanner (trace.rs) already extracts spec references (INV-*, ADR-*, NEG-*) from source code text using regex. The same technique applied to observation bodies would extract cross-references between observations. Once extracted as datom refs, the dependency graph becomes queryable: 'what does this finding depend on?', 'what does this finding enable?', 'what is the critical path through the findings?' SOLUTION: (1) In harvest.rs or a new observation_graph.rs, scan :exploration/body text for patterns: 'depends on|requires|prerequisite' + finding-ID, 'interacts with|relates to|strengthens' + finding-ID, 'enables|unblocks' + finding-ID. (2) Create :observation/depends-on (Ref, Many) and :observation/related-to (Ref, Many) datoms. (3) Expose via braid query for dependency chain traversal. VERIFICATION: After running on audit observations, the dependency chain F-ERR-003 -> F-INV-001 -> F-TYPE-001 -> F-C8-002 is queryable as a datom path. DEPENDENCIES: Independent. Feeds into C9-COMPONENT-3 (seed integration). FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/harvest.rs or new observation_graph.rs. EFFORT: 3h."
